ent":"0","text":"OTRAS CAUSAS → Toxicidad química directa: ↳\\NAmiodarona (41) ↳ Inhib. tirosina-quinasa:\\Nsunitinib/pazopanib/axitinib (42,43)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"301","parent":"0","text":"→ Tiroiditis\\Npost-radiación:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"302","parent":"0","text":"↳ Radiación externa","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"303","parent":"0","text":"↳ Post-radioyodo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"304","parent":"0","text":"→ Fármacos\\Ninmunomoduladores:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"305","parent":"0","text":"↳ IFN-α","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"306","parent":"0","text":"↳ Inhib. PD-1:\\Nnivolumab/pembrolizumab","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"307","parent":"0","text":"↳ Inhib. CTLA-4:\\Nipilimumab (44)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"308","parent":"0","text":"→ Otros:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"309","parent":"0","text":"↳ Vacuna\\NSARS-CoV-2 (Sd\\NASIA) (45)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"310","parent":"0","text":"↳ Litio","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"311","parent":"0","text":"↳ Palpación (ej:\\Ncirugía paratiroidea)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"312","parent":"0","text":"TRATAMIENTO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"313","parent":"0","text":"→ NO indicados:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"314","parent":"0","text":"↳ Antitiroideos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"315","parent":"0","text":"↳ Radioyodo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"316","parent":"0","text":"→ Manejo:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"317","parent":"0","text":"↳ β-bloqueantes:\\Ncontrol sintomático","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"318","parent":"0","text":"↳ Antiinflamatorios:\\NAAS/AINE/prednisona (casos\\Ngraves)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"319","parent":"0","text":"Copy","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"320","parent":"0","text":"Retry","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"321","parent":"0","text":"C","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"322","parent":"0","text":"EXOGENOUS AND ECTOPIC\\NHYPERTHYROIDISM","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"323","parent":"0","text":"Exogenous or ectopic hyperthyroidism (hyperthyroidism resulting from\\Nexcess thyroid hormone originating from outside the thyroid gland) can\\Narise from external or internal sources of excess thyroid hormone.\\NThyroidal blood flow on ultrasound and thyroid radioiodine uptake will\\Nbe low (table 1).","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"324","parent":"0","text":"Examples of exogenous\\Nhyperthyroidism include:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"325","parent":"0","text":"●Factitious ingestion of thyroid\\Nhormone. (See \"Exogenous\\Nhyperthyroidism\".)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"326","parent":"0","text":"●Acute hyperthyroidism from a levothyroxineoverdose. This\\Ndisorder can be ameliorated with beta blockers, drugs that\\Nblock the 5'-monodeiodinase (such as ipodate) and, in\\Nsevere cases, plasmapheresis or dialysis. (See \"Exogenous\\Nhyperthyroidism\".)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"327","parent":"0","text":"Examples of ectopic\\Nhyperthyroidism include:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"328","parent":"0","text":"●Struma ovarii, in which functioning thyroid tissue is\\Npresent in an ovarian neoplasm. Treatment consists of\\Novarian surgery. (See \"Struma ovarii\".)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"329","parent":"0","text":"●Functional thyroid cancer metastases, in which large, bony metastases\\Nfrom widely metastatic follicular thyroid cancer cause symptomatic\\Nhyperthyroidism. Treatment may require a variety of approaches including\\Nthionamides, radioiodine, surgery, or external radiotherapy. (See \"Follicular\\Nthyroid cancer (including oncocytic carcinoma of the thyroid)\", section on\\N'Metastases'.)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"330","parent":"0","text":"HIPERTIROIDISMO:\\NEXÓGENO Y ECTÓPICO","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"331","parent":"0","text":"CARACTERÍSTICAS\\NGENERALES","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"332","parent":"0","text":"→ Origen\\Nhormonal:\\Nextratiroidea","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"333","parent":"0","text":"→ Hallazgos:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"334","parent":"0","text":"↳ Flujo tiroideo eco: ↓","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"335","parent":"0","text":"↳ Captación\\Nradioyodo: ↓","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"336","parent":"0","text":"TIPOS","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"337","parent":"0","text":"EXÓGENO → Ingesta hormona\\Ntiroidea facticia → Sobredosis\\Nlevotiroxina: ↳ Tto:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"338","parent":"0","text":"β-bloqueantes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"339","parent":"0","text":"Inhib.\\N5'-monodesiodinasa\\N(ipodato)","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"340","parent":"0","text":"Casos graves:\\Nplasmaféresis/diálisis","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"341","parent":"0","text":"ECTÓPICO → Struma ovárico: ↳ Tejido\\Ntiroideo funcional en neoplasia ovárica\\N↳ Tto: cirugía ovárica","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"342","parent":"0","text":"→ Metástasis Ca\\Ntiroideo funcional:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"343","parent":"0","text":"↳ Localización:\\Nóseas grandes","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"344","parent":"0","text":"↳ Tipo: Ca\\Nfolicular\\Nmetastásico","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"345","parent":"0","text":"↳ Tto múltiple:","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"346","parent":"0","text":"- Antitiroideos","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"347","parent":"0","text":"- Radioyodo","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"348","parent":"0","text":"- Cirugía","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"349","parent":"0","text":"- RT externa","guid":"","children":[]}]},"node_count":349,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Endocrinología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Endocrinología","filename":"Basedow Graves-2024","id":"map_543","resolved_references":[]}